        <h2 style="color: var(--paper);">Get an insurance agent mortgage from a lender who reads captive W-2 commission, independent agent Schedule C, agency principal sub-producer override, carrier profit sharing, renewal income, and book-of-business economics as one file.</h2>
        <p style="color: rgba(250,250,247,0.78);">No application. No credit pull. A 20-minute conversation where we look at your captive W-2 if at State Farm/Allstate/Farmers/Liberty Mutual/Nationwide, your independent agent 1099-NEC if at Brown &amp; Brown/HUB/USI/Acrisure/regional agency, any agency principal S-corp 1120-S returns and K-1s if owner, your sub-producer agreements and override income if agency principal, your carrier profit-sharing distributions, your renewal income stream documentation, your state Department of Insurance licensure across all license lines, your carrier appointments, and any professional designation credentials (CPCU, CIC, CLU, ChFC, CFP) or MDRT credentialing &mdash; then we tell you whether Conventional Conforming W-2, Conventional Conforming Schedule C, Conventional Jumbo, S-Corp Self-Employed, or Bank Statement Non-QM fits best and roughly what the numbers look like. If we&rsquo;re not the right shop, we&rsquo;ll tell you that too.</p>
